description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advert for Support Manager – Urgent Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic and organised Urgent Care Support Manager as part of Morecambe Bay Clinical Commissioning Group (MBCCG) and the wider Health and Social Care System.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for supporting the Senior System Manager for Urgent Care and the wider Commissioning Team in the Morecambe Bay health and care system to ensure that it provides effective urgent care and achieves its constitutional targets. You will spend your time supporting the wider urgent care work streams in developing and updating project plans, drafting proposals, delivering pathway transformation and writing update reports – so excellent organisational and written communication skills are a must.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have great interpersonal skills as you will be engaging with people across all sectors of the health and social care economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working in a project or service transformation environment would be a real benefit, but full training will be given to the successful candidate. This role is ideal for an aspirational and ambitious individual who wants to go the extra mile to make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will also be required to undertake a variety of administrative tasks to support the team as and when required and these can include, but are not limited to; setting up meetings, managing diaries and taking minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, this role will also work with other commissioning work streams to assist in identifying opportunities for service improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to close this advert should we receive sufficient appropriate applications prior to the advertised closing date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal chat about the role, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tim Almond (Senior System Manager – Urgent Care)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;tim.almond@morecambebayccg.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;on 07498 374 228&lt;/p&gt;
